t his book <a href=\"http://unconsciousbranding.com/\">here</a>.\r\n\r\n<strong>Day 3 Party: Dropbox </strong>With lots of competing parties, where to go/ Dropbox at <a href=\"http://shop.mellowjohnnys.com/?gclid=CIiAle7Wr8QCFQ8waQodon4ALw\">Mellow Johnny\'s Bike Shop</a>, of course! Great party, and a great 90\'s cover band, Angry Flannel (which founder Drew Houston is a member of). Nirvana, Jane\'s Addiction, represented!\r\n\r\n<strong>Roundup - Day 4</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Panel: <em>Everything Eric Ries Has Learned Since 2011</em>, Eric Ries, Ted Greenwald</strong> Fans of <a href=\"http://theleanstartup.com/\">The Lean Startup</a> author, rejoice! Eric Ries announced a new book, crowd-sourced on Kickstarter, called <a href=\"http://www.fastcompany.com/3043745/most-creative-people/the-lean-startup-author-eric-ries-is-crowdsourcing-his-next-book-via-ki\">The Leader\'s Guide</a>. Don\'t be intimidated - just be entertained - by the number of special \'packages\' you can choose from - it\'s part of the gimmick! For reference, I went with the All-Access Package.\r\n\r\nQuick shout out to my new friends at Tech.co, Chute, Partnered, and General Assembly - great meeting you guys. Rock on, Austin, and see you in 2016!','Hello from Austin and another SXSW!','','inherit','open','open','','254-revision-v1','','','2015-03-18 20:07:44','2015-03-18 20:07:44','',254,'http://abbot-water.dev/254-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
